configuring vim on new computer:

1. Add colorschemes manually (vundle fails for some reason):
    $ mkdir ~/.vim
    $ git clone https://github.com/flazz/vim-colorschemes ~/.vim

2. clone vundle:
    $ git clone https://github.com/gmarik/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim

3. create symlink to .vimrc and .xxx_header.txt files:
    $ ln -s ~/dotfiles/.vimrc .vimrc
    $ ln -s ~/dotfiles/.h_header.txt .h_header.txt
    $ ln -s ~/dotfiles/.py_header.txt .py_header.txt
    $ ln -s ~/dotfiles/.c_header.txt .c_header.txt
    $ ln -s ~/dotfiles/.cpp_header.txt .cpp_header.txt
    $ ln -s ~/dotfiles/.cc_header.txt .cc_header.txt

3. launch vundle to install all plugins: 
    $ vim +PluginInstall +qall
